    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      66.14,
      117.6,
      537.67,
      132.8
    ],
    "text": "The 4'h Accused-Appellant-Petitioner-Petitioner (hereinafter referred to as the Petitioner) was",
    "fonts": [
      "Helvetica",
      "Times-Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      9.91797161102295,
      11.296782493591309,
      11.399999618530273
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      65.71,
      132.71,
      538.2,
      238.28
    ],
    "text": "indicted with three other accused under Section 296 read with Section 32 of the Penal Code before the High Court of Panadura. The Petitioner and other accused pleaded not guilty to the charge, and thereafter the trial had commenced. At the conclusion of the trial, after considering submissions of all parties made before the Court, the Learned High Court Judge ofPanadura had delivered the Judgment on 14.02.2019, convicting the Petitioner and other three accused under Section 316 of the Penal Code, read with Section 32 of the same. Accordingly, the following sentence had been imposed on the Petitioner and each accused;",
    "fonts": [
      "Times-Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.399999618530273,
      11.446206092834473,
      11.746241569519043,
      11.947025299072266
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      80.95,
      246.47,
      313.58,
      261.67
    ],
    "text": "I. A term of 05 years rigorous imprisonment,",
    "fonts": [
      "Times-Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      7.699999809265137,
      11.399999618530273,
      11.947025299072266
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      77.34,
      276.35,
      503.94,
      291.55
    ],
    "text": "II. A fine of Rs. 10,000/= with a default sentence of 03 months simple imprisonment.",
    "fonts": [
      "Times-Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      7.979574680328369,
      11.231961250305176,
      11.399999618530273,
      11.947025299072266
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      65.31,
      299.4,
      539.57,
      374.72
    ],
    "text": "Being aggrieved by the said judgment, the Petitioner had filed an appeal in this Court on 01.03 .2019. Thereafter, the Petitioner had filed a Bail Pending Appeal on 08.03.2019 under Section 20(2) of the Bail Act NO.30 of 1997. The Learned High Court Judge of Panadura had refused the said Bail Pending Appeal Application by order dated 14.03.2019 on the ground of previous convictions and jump bail.",
    "fonts": [
      "Times-Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.352048873901367,
      11.399999618530273,
      11.41938304901123,
      11.502737045288086,
      11.947025299072266
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      65.04,
      380.59,
      535.86,
      398.32
    ],
    "text": "On failing to succeed with the 1st Bail Pending Appeal Application, the Petitioner made the 2nd",
    "fonts": [
      "Helvetica",
      "Times-Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      7.641844749450684,
      7.800099849700928,
      11.296782493591309,
      11.399999618530273
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      64.73,
      397.68,
      537.38,
      442.76
    ],
    "text": "Bail Pending Appeal application in the High Court on 29.03.2019. The Learned High Court Judge of Panadura had refused the said 2nd Bail Pending Appeal Application by order dated 29.03.20 19 and thereby the Petitioner has fi led the instant case in this Court.",
    "fonts": [
      "Helvetica",
      "Times-Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      7.2970991134643555,
      10.835840225219727,
      11.0,
      11.153024673461914,
      11.399999618530273,
      11.746241569519043
    ]
  },
