    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      65.04,
      474.36,
      325.95,
      489.56
    ],
    "text": "Grounds of the Revision Application by Petitioner",
    "fonts": [
      "Times-Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.399999618530273,
      11.409396171569824,
      11.53994083404541,
      11.541916847229004,
      11.617818832397461
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      64.34,
      520.43,
      536.95,
      565.51
    ],
    "text": "The Petitioner, in his Petition dated 07.06.2019, has averred that the order of the Learned High Court Judge of Panadura refusing to enlarge the Petitioner on Bail Pending Appeal has erred in law on several grounds, as stated by paragraph 9 of the said Petition as follows;",
    "fonts": [
      "Times-Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.153024673461914,
      11.296782493591309,
      11.399999618530273,
      11.947025299072266,
      12.144536972045898
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      115.51,
      596.39,
      422.17,
      611.59
    ],
    "text": "I. Failed to consider the law relating to Bail Pending Appeal",
    "fonts": [
      "Times-Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      7.699999809265137,
      11.399999618530273
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      172.71,
      615.48,
      177.01,
      624.82
    ],
    "text": "\"",
    "fonts": [
      "Helvetica"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      6.800099849700928
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      111.71,
      626.63,
      498.67,
      641.83
    ],
    "text": "II. Failed to consider the exceptional circumstances averred by the Petitioner",
    "fonts": [
      "Helvetica",
      "Times-Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      8.123421669006348,
      11.296782493591309,
      11.352048873901367,
      11.399999618530273
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      108.44,
      656.15,
      488.62,
      671.35
    ],
    "text": "Ill. Failed to consider the substantial miscarriage of justice to the Petitioner",
    "fonts": [
      "Helvetica",
      "Times-Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      8.632927894592285,
      11.399999618530273,
      11.947025299072266
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      273.75,
      735.71,
      325.69,
      748.76
    ],
    "text": "Page 4 of 8",
    "fonts": [
      "Helvetica"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      9.5,
      9.959583282470703
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      110.46,
      72.18,
      536.76,
      116.52
    ],
    "text": "IV. Failed to consider the actual peri09 of imprisonment to be served by the Petitioner in light of the Prison Regulations made under Section 94(1) of the Prison Ordinance",
    "fonts": [
      "Times-Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      8.399999618530273,
      11.005295753479004,
      11.100000381469727,
      11.788779258728027,
      11.98362922668457
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      64.74,
      171.03,
      141.81,
      186.5
    ],
    "text": "Legal Analysis",
    "fonts": [
      "Times-Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.600000381469727
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      76.07,
      217.83,
      403.37,
      233.3
    ],
    "text": "I. Failed to consider the law relating to Bail Pending Appeal.",
    "fonts": [
      "Helvetica",
      "Times-Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      8.185327529907227,
      11.600000381469727,
      11.624025344848633,
      11.714089393615723
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      63.92,
      256.14,
      536.34,
      300.84
    ],
    "text": "The Learned Counsel for the Petitioner in his submission before the High Court of Panadura, on 29.03.2019, has submitted the case of Dachchini Vs. Attorney General (2005) 2 SLR 152, in support of his Bail Pending Appeal Application.",
    "fonts": [
      "Times-Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.100000381469727,
      11.14690113067627,
      11.788779258728027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      64.37,
      309.42,
      317.49,
      324.23
    ],
    "text": "In Dachchini V s. Attorney General, it was held that,",
    "fonts": [
      "Times-Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      10.832168579101562,
      11.100000381469727
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      62.86,
      356.33,
      535.91,
      400.98
    ],
    "text": "\" By the enactment oJthe Bail Act the policy in granting bail has undergone a major change. The rule is the grant oj bail. The rule upholds the values endorsed in humanJreedom. The exception is the reJusal oJbail and reasons should be given when reJusing the bail ...",
    "fonts": [
      "Times-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.276801109313965,
      11.464994430541992,
      11.60854721069336,
      11.66679859161377,
      11.784039497375488,
      11.800000190734863,
      12.979499816894531
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      61.94,
      409.61,
      536.37,
      498.91
    ],
    "text": "Per SRISKANDARAJAH, J: By the enactment oj the Bail Act there is a major change in the legislative policy and the Courts are bound to give effect to this policy. The High Court Judge in the impugned Order has erred in not taking into consideration the policy changes that has been brought in by the enactment and mechanically applied the principle that the accused have Jailed to show exceptional circumstances when this requirement is no more a principle governing bail pending appeal ... \"",
    "fonts": [
      "Times-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.427727699279785,
      11.52269172668457,
      11.569753646850586,
      11.60854721069336,
      11.76284122467041,
      11.770513534545898,
      11.792947769165039,
      11.800000190734863,
      12.979499816894531
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      62.53,
      530.47,
      535.69,
      575.16
    ],
    "text": "However, the contention that was held in the Court of Appeal by Dachchini Vs. Attorney General was overruled by the Supreme Court judgment of Attorney General Vs. Letchchemi & Another (SC Appeal 13/2006) (2006 BLR 16), where it was held that,",
    "fonts": [
      "Helvetica",
      "Times-Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      10.800000190734863,
      11.100000381469727,
      11.225836753845215,
      11.338390350341797,
      11.98362922668457
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      61.78,
      592.24,
      539.28,
      651.19
    ],
    "text": "\" The presumption oj innocence that ensures in Javour oj those suspected or accused or connected with the commission oj an offence, cease to operate after conviction by a court oj competent jurisdiction.\"",
    "fonts": [
      "Helvetica",
      "Times-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.52269172668457,
      11.60854721069336,
      11.66679859161377,
      11.800000190734863,
      12.775110244750977,
      12.979499816894531,
      16.70009994506836
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      62.37,
      658.98,
      176.52,
      673.79
    ],
    "text": "[t was further held that,",
    "fonts": [
      "Times-Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.100000381469727
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      61.42,
      681.86,
      535.4,
      712.03
    ],
    "text": "\"Bail after conviction in the High Court reJerred to in Section 333(3) oJ the Code oj Criminal Procedure Act No. 15 oJ1979 has been incorporated in verbatim in Section 20(2) oj the Bail Act",
    "fonts": [
      "Times-Italic",
      "Times-Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.360100746154785,
      11.399999618530273,
      11.52269172668457,
      11.600000381469727,
      11.60854721069336,
      11.800000190734863,
      11.820432662963867,
      12.775110244750977
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      271.95,
      735.7,
      323.89,
      748.75
    ],
    "text": "Page 5 of 8",
    "fonts": [
      "Helvetica"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      9.5,
      9.959583282470703
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      64.7,
      71.97,
      536.62,
      131.71
    ],
    "text": "No. 30 of 1997. The sellied law on this is that wfzere a section has been incorporated in verbatim, governing principles applicable are those contained in the principle enactment. The interpretation of the principle enactment has always held that there must be exceptional circumstances.",
    "fonts": [
      "Times-Italic",
      "Times-Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.100000381469727,
      11.224043846130371,
      11.300000190734863,
      11.60854721069336,
      11.66679859161377,
      11.784039497375488,
      11.800000190734863,
      12.979499816894531
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      64.02,
      140.01,
      537.64,
      185.35
    ],
    "text": "As section 20 of the Bail Act No. 30 of 1997 is identical to that contained in the Code of Crimina I Procedure, in its implementation the earlier restricted view of the convicted person having to disclose exceptional circumstances for grant of bail must prevail ... \"",
    "fonts": [
      "Times-Italic",
      "Times-Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.300000190734863,
      11.360100746154785,
      11.365212440490723,
      11.511226654052734,
      11.52269172668457,
      11.569753646850586,
      11.770513534545898,
      11.800000190734863,
      12.775110244750977,
      12.979499816894531
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      63.98,
      216.7,
      535.65,
      246.53
    ],
    "text": "Thus, it is a proven fact that exceptional circumstances must prevail to grant bail for a convicted person. Therefore the Petitioner should prove exceptional circumstances.",
    "fonts": [
      "Times-Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      10.912971496582031,
      11.015827178955078,
      11.247126579284668,
      11.248181343078613,
      11.300000190734863
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      72.28,
      278.26,
      484.95,
      294.01
    ],
    "text": "ii. Failed to consider the exceptional circumstances averred bv the Petitioner.",
    "fonts": [
      "Times-Bold",
      "Times-BoldItalic",
      "Times-Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.119711875915527,
      11.300000190734863
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      63.34,
      316.06,
      534.63,
      346.25
    ],
    "text": "As it was stated in Javanthi Silva and Two Others Vs. Attorney General (1997) 3 SLR 11 7, by D.P.S.Gunasekera J.,",
    "fonts": [
      "Times-Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      10.232584953308105,
      11.104000091552734,
      11.300000190734863
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      61.44,
      354.89,
      535.87,
      384.43
    ],
    "text": "\"Over the years a principle has evolved through judicial decisions that bail pending appeal from convictions by the Supreme Court would only be granted in exceptional circumstances.\"",
    "fonts": [
      "Times-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.531085968017578,
      11.60854721069336,
      11.722042083740234,
      11.784039497375488,
      11.800000190734863
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      62.57,
      415.78,
      535.69,
      445.64
    ],
    "text": "This fact has been held in many other judicial presidents such as Attorney General Vs. Ediriweera (SC Appeal No. 100/2005) (2006 BLR 12), where it was held that,",
    "fonts": [
      "Helvetica-Oblique",
      "Times-Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.300000190734863,
      11.440081596374512
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      62.14,
      477.18,
      535.03,
      506.82
    ],
    "text": "\"The norm is that bail ajier conviclion is not a mailer of right but would be granted only under exceptional circumstances.\"",
    "fonts": [
      "Times-Italic",
      "Times-Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.100000381469727,
      11.76284122467041,
      11.784039497375488,
      11.800000190734863,
      12.979499816894531
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      62.59,
      538.18,
      457.02,
      553.26
    ],
    "text": "Further, in the case ofMuthuretty Vs. The Oueen (54 NLR 493), it was held that,",
    "fonts": [
      "Times-Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.015827178955078,
      11.104000091552734,
      11.300000190734863,
      11.333949089050293,
      11.39777660369873
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      61.78,
      561.89,
      535.22,
      591.43
    ],
    "text": "\"That in bail pending appeal, Court will not grant bail as a rule, bail granted only in exceptional circumstances .. . \"",
    "fonts": [
      "Times-BoldItalic",
      "Times-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.0,
      11.353399276733398,
      11.60854721069336,
      11.800000190734863
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      62.26,
      601.63,
      534.55,
      652.26
    ],
    "text": ".. As exceptional circumstances the Learned Counsel has submitted that the Petitioner is a married man with children and the Petitioner is unable to support the family.",
    "fonts": [
      "Helvetica",
      "Times-Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      10.55120849609375,
      11.300000190734863
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      61.8,
      660.21,
      535.43,
      719.94
    ],
    "text": "The grounds submitted by the Learned Counsel for the Petitioner to the fact that his wife and children would be destitute if the Petitioner is not at the matrimonial house, does not amount to an \"exceptional circumstance\". This aspect was considered by L.T.B.Dehideniya J. Ranil Charuka Kulathunga Vs. Attorney General (CA [PHC] APN 134/2015).",
    "fonts": [
      "Times-Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.011466026306152,
      11.085565567016602,
      11.247126579284668,
      11.259928703308105,
      11.300000190734863,
      11.342071533203125,
      11.789880752563477
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      271.59,
      735.71,
      323.89,
      748.76
    ],
    "text": "Page 6 of 8",
    "fonts": [
      "Helvetica"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      9.428278923034668,
      9.5,
      9.959583282470703
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 6,
    "bbox": [
      65.55,
      71.21,
      539.04,
      115.5
    ],
    "text": "\"The Petitioner submits several grounds as exceptionpl grounds to consider bail. The Petitioner states that he is a married person with two school going children. A person gelling married and having children is not an exceptional ground. It is the normal day to day life of the people. \"",
    "fonts": [
      "Times-Italic",
      "Times-Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.100000381469727,
      11.22803783416748,
      11.409333229064941,
      11.464994430541992,
      11.76284122467041,
      11.770513534545898,
      11.800000190734863,
      12.979499816894531
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 6,
    "bbox": [
      65.62,
      146.9,
      476.61,
      162.37
    ],
    "text": "III. Failed to consider the substantial miscarriage of justice to the Petitioner.",
    "fonts": [
      "Helvetica",
      "Times-Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      8.360486030578613,
      11.39544677734375,
      11.600000381469727,
      11.745141983032227,
      11.848831176757812
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 6,
    "bbox": [
      65.06,
      193.76,
      537.64,
      223.46
    ],
    "text": "Though it is submitted that there is a miscarriage of justice the counsel is unable to support his versIon.",
    "fonts": [
      "Times-Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      10.962635040283203,
      10.966976165771484,
      11.197249412536621,
      11.199999809265137,
      12.037534713745117
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 6,
    "bbox": [
      65.26,
      231.56,
      482.99,
      246.5
    ],
    "text": "[n the case of .Iayanthi Silva and Two Others Vs. Attorney General (1997) 3 SLR 1[ 7,",
    "fonts": [
      "Times-Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      10.95113468170166,
      11.027470588684082,
      11.04908275604248,
      11.199999809265137,
      11.238035202026367,
      11.841763496398926
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 6,
    "bbox": [
      64.36,
      278.57,
      536.8,
      322.99
    ],
    "text": "\"The appellate court would interfere where a Judge has given weight to considerations which are irrelevant or taken into account extraneous considerations in exerCising his discretion which would amount to an abuse of the discretion vested to act judicially. \"",
    "fonts": [
      "Times-Italic",
      "Times-Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.552606582641602,
      11.60854721069336,
      11.735221862792969,
      11.770513534545898,
      11.800000190734863,
      11.891048431396484,
      12.979499816894531
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 6,
    "bbox": [
      63.98,
      354.32,
      536.53,
      414.26
    ],
    "text": "Therefore it is evident that the law relating to bail pending appeal had been correctly applied by the Learned High Court Judge and it is only at the absence of any exceptional circumstances as it has been est:lblished by legal principles over years, that the Learned High Court Judge had refused the Application on bail pending appeal.",
    "fonts": [
      "Times-Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      10.585650444030762,
      10.819537162780762,
      10.958189010620117,
      10.966976165771484,
      11.077682495117188,
      11.198299407958984,
      11.199999809265137,
      12.037534713745117
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 6,
    "bbox": [
      64.18,
      422.36,
      302.19,
      437.3
    ],
    "text": "[n the instant case, the Judge has acted judicially.",
    "fonts": [
      "Times-Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      10.907530784606934,
      11.027470588684082,
      11.197249412536621,
      11.199999809265137,
      11.204399108886719
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 6,
    "bbox": [
      62.54,
      445.76,
      536.63,
      475.83
    ],
    "text": "Having made a Revision Application to this Court, the Petitioner has to invoke the revisionary jurisdiction of this Court, which is to be exercised only under exceptional circumstances.",
    "fonts": [
      "Times-Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.197249412536621,
      11.199999809265137,
      11.841763496398926
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 6,
    "bbox": [
      63.28,
      506.96,
      424.9,
      521.91
    ],
    "text": "In Attorney General Vs. Gunawardena (1996) 2 SLR 149 it was held that,",
    "fonts": [
      "Times-Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      10.966976165771484,
      11.199999809265137,
      11.291476249694824
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 6,
    "bbox": [
      62.5,
      530.58,
      536.2,
      544.99
    ],
    "text": "\"Revision like an appeal is directed towards the correction of errors but it is supervisory in",
    "fonts": [
      "Times-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.635503768920898,
      11.735574722290039,
      11.76284122467041,
      11.800000190734863,
      11.850293159484863,
      12.979499816894531
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 6,
    "bbox": [
      62.88,
      545.69,
      536.35,
      574.87
    ],
    "text": "nature and its object is the due administration of justice and not primarily or solely the relieving of grievances of a party ... \"",
    "fonts": [
      "Times-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.569753646850586,
      11.60854721069336,
      11.76284122467041,
      11.770513534545898,
      11.800000190734863,
      12.775110244750977,
      12.979499816894531
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 6,
    "bbox": [
      62.59,
      606.32,
      535.43,
      621.26
    ],
    "text": "Further in the case of Bank of Ceylon Vs. Kaleel and Others (2004) ISLR 284, as it was held by",
    "fonts": [
      "Times-Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.047917366027832,
      11.054758071899414,
      11.199999809265137,
      11.31179141998291,
      11.841763496398926,
      12.037534713745117
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 6,
    "bbox": [
      63.68,
      621.08,
      153.57,
